https://www.facebook.com/groups/madhurasrecipe/Jwariche noodles is a traditional recipe. It is healthy too as we are using jwari and lot many veggies. It is as good as having bhakari and bhaji wih a little twist. Your kids will love this recipe. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 1 cup Jawar flour‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ Hot Water‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Oil‚Ä¢ Cumin seeds‚Ä¢ Curry leaves‚Ä¢ Hing‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Garlic‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Onion‚Ä¢ Chopped Beans‚Ä¢ Fresh peas‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Tomato‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Capsicum‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Carrot‚Ä¢ Garam masala‚Ä¢ Coriander powder‚Ä¢ Turmeric powder‚Ä¢ Red chili powder‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ Water‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Coriander leavesMethod:‚Ä¢ Take jawar flour in a bowl and add salt. Mix well.‚Ä¢ Add hot water and mix well. ‚Ä¢ When the mixture cools down a little, knead a little stiff dough like bhakati dough. ‚Ä¢ You can add turmeric powder, ajwain in the dough if you want. ‚Ä¢ Roll the dough into a roll and transfer it into chakali mould. ‚Ä¢ Fit medium thick shev dish in the mould. ‚Ä¢ Grease a dish well with oil. ‚Ä¢ Roll kurdai like noodles into the plate. ‚Ä¢ Heat up water at the base of the steamer. ‚Ä¢ Transfer the dish into upper pot and steam on medium heat for about 10-12 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Take the dish out.‚Ä¢ Heat up oil in a pan. ‚Ä¢ Add cumin seeds and let them splutter. ‚Ä¢ Add curry leaves, hing, garlic and fry for about 2 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Add onion, beans, fresh peas and fry everything for about 5-6 minutes. ‚Ä¢ After frying for about 3-4 minutes add tomato, capsicum, carrot and fry everything for about 3-  4 minutes. ‚Ä¢ When veggies are fried well add garam masala, coriander powder, turmeric powder, red chili   powder and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Add salt and fry for another 2 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Add water and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Break the steamed noodles and add. ‚Ä¢ You can add noodles as it is. ‚Ä¢ Mix well, cover and steam for about 4-5 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Add coriander leaves and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Jwariche noodles are all ready. ‚Ä¢ You can have these as it is or serve with a slice of lemon. ‚Ä¢ You can add sauces like soya sauce, chili sauce, tomato sauce in place of spices if you want   for variation. ‚Ä¢ You can have this at any time of the day. ‚Ä¢ This recipe is good for diabetic people or people on diet. Second Headline-Rick Bright, Director of America's Biomedical Advanced Research and Development Authority (BARDA) was removed from his post. Rick Bright says he was demoted over doubts on Hydroxychloroquine, a malaria drug Donald Trump is promoting. Third Headline-Li Zehua, a citizen journalist in China who disappeared in February following his reporting on Coronavirus outbreak (COVID-19) in Wuhan, reappeared on April 22. Badi Khabar-Sweden, a country in Northern Europe known popularly as Scandinavia, has adopted a different approach to contain Coronavirus pandemic (COVID-19). Sweden did not go into lockdown. All businesses there are open, including restaurants, bars, and markets and under-16 schools. Sweden advised people to maintain social distancing and urged older people to avoid social contacts. But, for a longer period of time these suggestions were voluntary. Sweden's corona strategy is guided not by the Swedish government. Government follows the expert recommendations given by Sweden's Public Health Agency. Anders Tegnell, Chief epidemiologist at Sweden's Public Health Agency is the main architect behind Sweden's controversial Coronavirus strategy. Anders Tegnell favors the herd immunity approach. Anders Tegnell claims that each country in the world has to reach herd community. We are using rava or sooji in this recipe to make it quick and instant one. It tastes just awesome and healthy recipe too. This can be a quick evening or tea time snack. You can give this in lunch box for your little ones. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup fine Sooji‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup Curd‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Besan‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Water‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp Turmeric powder‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Coriander powder‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Red chili powder‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Finely chopped Capsicum‚Ä¢ 2 tsp finely chopped Tomato‚Ä¢ 2~3 tsp Mint leaves‚Ä¢ Finley chopped Green chili‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Eno fruit salt‚Ä¢ Water ‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Oil‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Mustard seeds‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds‚Ä¢ Curry leaves‚Ä¢ White sesame seeds‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Coriander leavesMethod:‚Ä¢ Take sooji in a bowl. ‚Ä¢ Add curd, besan, salt and mix everything well together. ‚Ä¢ You can use buttermilk or lemon juice in place of curd. ‚Ä¢ Add water and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Add turmeric powder, coriander powder, red chili powder, capsicum, tomato, mint leaves, green   chili and mix well. ‚Ä¢ You can use veggies of your choice. ‚Ä¢ You can use coriander leaves in place of mint leaves. ‚Ä¢ Cover and rest the batter for about 15-20 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Mix the batter well once more. ‚Ä¢ Add eno, water and mix well. ‚Ä¢ You can add 1/4 tsp baking soda in place of Eno. ‚Ä¢ Heat up oil in a pan. ‚Ä¢ Add mustard seeds and let them pop up. ‚Ä¢ Add cumin seeds, curry leaves, white sesame seeds and mix well once. ‚Ä¢ Add the batter at the center of the tadka and spread it evenly. ‚Ä¢ Cover and cook on low heat for about 8-10 minutes until lower side is cooked well. ‚Ä¢ Remove the lid and flip over the hadvdo into a dish. ‚Ä¢ In the same pan add a little oil and slide the handvo into the pan. ‚Ä¢ You can add tadka again if you want. ‚Ä¢ Cook for another 3-4 minutes until other side is cooked well. ‚Ä¢ When handvo is cooked well from both sides take it out into a dish. ‚Ä¢ Garnish with coriander leaves and cut it into pieces. ‚Ä¢ Rava handvo is all ready.Please take a moment to like and subscribehttps://www.youtube.com/user/madhura94?sub_confirmation=1‚úø‚óï ‚Äø ‚óï‚úøFor more Such RecipesSamosa Pinwheels | Crispy Samosa Roll | Aloo Bhakarwadi | MadhurasRecipe Ep -
